# anneal-memory CLI ‚Äî LEAN Agent-Instructions Snippet
#
# Paste the section below into your harness's agent-instructions file
# (CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md / GEMINI.md). This is the always-loaded MINIMUM ‚Äî
# the workflow an agent needs to act correctly. For the full reference
# (immune-system internals, affective-state shape, operator commands),
# install the anneal-memory SKILL (skill/anneal-memory/SKILL.md), which
# loads on-demand, or see examples/agent-instructions.full.cli.example.
#
# Requires: pip install anneal-memory; set ANNEAL_MEMORY_DB (or use --db).

## Memory (anneal-memory CLI)

This project uses anneal-memory for persistent memory across sessions ‚Äî
four retrospective layers (episodes compress into continuity; Hebbian
links + a limbic tag form automatically) plus a **spore** store for
prospective open loops (`task`/`question`/`thought`, planted then
resolved) and an on-demand **crystallized** tier that holds proven, stable
patterns *out* of always-loaded context and surfaces them on cue (opt-in +
harness-fired ‚Äî see the SKILL or full snippet). Use memory naturally; don't
narrate the tooling.

**Start:** `anneal-memory continuity` (run `anneal-memory init` first if
the DB doesn't exist). If it prints "No continuity file yet" and exits
non-zero, this is the first session ‚Äî just start recording (not an error).

**During work:** record as things happen ‚Äî the *reasoning*, not just the
fact:
  anneal-memory record "Chose X because Y" --type decision
Types: decision ¬∑ observation ¬∑ tension ¬∑ question ¬∑ outcome ¬∑ context.
Record proactively; target 5‚Äì15 episodes a session. Plant a spore the
moment a loop opens: `anneal-memory spore add --type task --text "‚Ä¶"`.

**Before decisions (NON-NEGOTIABLE):** `anneal-memory recall "<surface
area>"` and integrate what comes back. If nothing returns, proceed and
note recall fired clean. Skipping this is the dead-store failure mode ‚Äî
the store grows while decisions get made blind to it.

**Wrap (at "wrap up" / "save memory" / "we're done"):** run the full
sequence, once ‚Äî `anneal-memory prepare-wrap` ‚Üí compress per its
instructions (this step IS the thinking; principles over facts) ‚Üí
`anneal-memory save-continuity continuity.md`. Demoted graduations are
the validation pipeline working, not an error; don't re-run to chase a
clean report. Cite real episode IDs honestly ‚Äî you are the first line of
defense, the library is the second.

**Operator inspection:** `status` ¬∑ `stats` ¬∑ `graph` ¬∑ `history` ¬∑
`audit` ¬∑ `verify` ¬∑ `export` (all support `--json`).

**Staying current:** after upgrading the package, run `anneal-memory
migrate check` ‚Äî it proposes edits to *these* instructions so they don't
drift from the substrate (it never edits your files); then `migrate ack`.
